play and a separate smaller color touchscreen that serves as the primary input device and was capable of wifi and att g wireless connectivity the original nook was followed in november  by a color lcd device called the nook color in june  by the nook simple touch and in november  and february  by the nook tablet on april   barnes  noble entered into a partnership with microsoft that spun off the nook and college businesses into a subsidiary on august   barnes and noble announced partnerships with retailers in the uk which began offering the nook digital products in october  in december  bn purchased microsofts nook shares ending the partnership nook users may read nearly any nook store ebook digital magazines or newspapers for one hour once per day while connected to the stores wifi contents  naming  devices  current  nook glowlight plus e ink  samsung galaxy tab nook  samsung galaxy tab  nook  lcd  samsung galaxy tab s nook  lcd  samsung galaxy tab e nook  lcd  nook tablet   discontinued  nook st edition e ink  g  wifi version  wifi version  nook simple touch e ink  nook simple touch with glowlight e ink  nook color lcd  nook tablet lcd  nook hd and nook hd  nook hd  nook hd  samsung galaxy tab  nook  lcd  nook glowlight e ink  features and specifications  sales  nook ereader applications for third party devices  nook free reading applications  nook for web  nookstudy and yuzu  nookstudy  yuzu  issues  compatibility issues  locked file table  lending restrictions  downloading of nook store content  spinoff of business  see also  references  external links namingedit the nook name and identity was devised and created by the brand development group at rga nook was initially rejected as a name by barnes  noble but eventually the connection to nook being a familiar place to read was compelling enough to change the minds of the companys executives this decision pivoted on the information contained within an npr article which suggested that women readers tend to read more than men the name is also claimed by rex wilder when he was consulting for ammunition design group the name was among over  he created although that naming project ended with no name being chosen devicesedit currentedit nook glowlight plus e inkedit the nook glowlight plus ereader was released on october   and it features a inch ppi carta e ink screen with frontlight and touchscreen wifi an aluminum rear shell six weeks of battery  mah life with wireless off weights  ounces and meets ip meaning it is waterproof for up to  minutes at a maximum depth of  meter and is dustproof the nook software is run on android  kitkat and it has gb of useraccessible storage the glowlight plus uses a freescale imx  ghz cpu and has mb ram since the device runs android  third party apps and launchers can be installed due to the lack of physical buttons initial set up to install third party apps is done through a usb connection to a computer samsung galaxy tab nookedit in february  bn announced a new nook color tablet would be released in  in june  barnes  noble announced it would be teaming up with samsung to develop cobranded tablets titled the samsung galaxy tab  nook the devices would feature samsungs hardware with a inch display and customized nook software from barnes  noble samsung galaxy tab  nook  lcdedit the galaxy tab  nook was released in the us in august   with bns nook division focusing on the software and content and samsung focusing on the hardware the product uses android  kitkat on a  ghz quadcore snapdragon soc with  gb ram wifi and bluetooth and features a  mp frontfacing camera a  mp rear camera screen resolution of  ×  and a microsd storage slot that accepts cards up to gb it launched with a us retail price in may  the price was reduced to citation needed samsung galaxy tab s nook  lcdedit in september  bn released the samsung galaxy tab s nook which is a nook branded samsung galaxy tab s  lcd tablet that includes some samsung and bn software it uses android  and