 edition e ink  g  wifi version  wifi version  nook simple touch e ink  nook simple touch with glowlight e ink  nook color lcd  nook tablet lcd  nook hd and nook hd  nook hd  nook hd  samsung galaxy tab  nook  lcd  nook glowlight e ink  features and specifications  sales  nook ereader applications for third party devices  nook free reading applications  nook for web  nookstudy and yuzu  nookstudy  yuzu  issues  compatibility issues  locked file table  lending restrictions  downloading of nook store content  spinoff of business  see also  references  external links namingedit the nook name and identity was devised and created by the brand development group at rga nook was initially rejected as a name by barnes  noble but eventually the connection to nook being a familiar place to read was compelling enough to change the minds of the companys executives this decision pivoted on the information contained within an npr article which suggested that women readers tend to read more than men the name is also claimed by rex wilder when he was consulting for ammunition design group the name was among over  he created although that naming project ended with no name being chosen devicesedit currentedit nook glowlight plus e inkedit the nook glowlight plus ereader was released on october   and it features a inch ppi carta e ink screen with frontlight and touchscreen wifi an aluminum rear shell six weeks of battery  mah life with wireless off weights  ounces and meets ip meaning it is waterproof for up to  minutes at a maximum depth of  meter and is dustproof the nook software is run on android  kitkat and it has gb of useraccessible storage the glowlight plus uses a freescale imx  ghz cpu and has mb ram since the device runs android  third party apps and launchers can be installed due to the lack of physical buttons initial set up to install third party apps is done through a usb connection to a computer samsung galaxy tab nookedit in february  bn announced a new nook color tablet would be released in  in june  barnes  noble announced it would be teaming up with samsung to develop cobranded tablets titled the samsung galaxy tab  nook the devices would feature samsungs hardware with a inch display and customized nook software from barnes  noble samsung galaxy tab  nook  lcdedit the galaxy tab  nook was released in the us in august   with bns nook division focusing on the software and content and samsung focusing on the hardware the product uses android  kitkat on a  ghz quadcore snapdragon soc with  gb ram wifi and bluetooth and features a  mp frontfacing camera a  mp rear camera screen resolution of  ×  and a microsd storage slot that accepts cards up to gb it launched with a us retail price in may  the price was reduced to citation needed samsung galaxy tab s nook  lcdedit in september  bn released the samsung galaxy tab s nook which is a nook branded samsung galaxy tab s  lcd tablet that includes some samsung and bn software it uses android  and features an core cpu  ghz quad   ghz quad with gb ram gb of internal storage a microsd card slot two cameras mp front and mp rear and a  mah battery which bn says will last for up to  hours of video usage and launched with a us retail price samsung galaxy tab e nook  lcdedit in october  bn released the samsung galaxy tab e nook which is a nook branded samsung galaxy tab  lcd tablet that includes some samsung bn and microsoft software this tablet runs android  on a  ghz qualcomm snapdragon  cpu with gb of storage microsd card support weighs  grams and two cameras mp front and mp rear and its  display has a resolution of  x  and it retails for  nook tablet edit in november  bn released the nook tablet  which is a nookbranded tablet with a  screen that has a resolution of  x  and retails at  it is using android  marshmallow with nook apps included with a ghz mediatek cpu it has gb storage a microsd card slot wifi and bluetooth it weighs  ounces and has a battery for up to  hours discontinuededit nook st edition e inkedit main article barnes  noble nook st edition the device has two versions a nook that includes wifi and att g wireless connectivity and one that only includes wifi g  wifi versionedit this version made its debut on november   at a retail price of us it was offered with builtin wifi  g connectivity for free access to the barnes  noble online store this has a sixinch e ink display and a separate smaller color touchscreen that serves as the primary input device the price was dropped to us on june   upon the release of the new nook wifi with the announcement of the newer nook simple touch reader on may   the price was dropped to us in early  nook wifi  g was discontinued wifi versionedit this version of the nook st edition supports only wifi not g wireless and is easily distinguishable due to its white back panel in contrast to the gray back panel of the wifi  g version nook wifi made its debut on june   at a retail price of us with the announcement of the newer nook simple touch reader on may   the price was dropped to us in september  the price was dropped again to us in late  nook wifi was discontinued nook simple touch e inkedit main article nook simple touch announced on may   the simple touch reader also informally referred as nook nd edition was released on june   at a retail price of us the simple touch is a wifi only nook with an infrared touchscreen e ink technology and battery life of up to two months or  hours offering approximately  continuous page turns with wifi turned off the device weighs  grams  oz with dimensions of  ×  ×  on november   the simple touch readers price dropped to us on december   the simple touch readers price dropped to us on december   the simple touch readers price dropped to us in february  the simple touch reader was discontinued due to being phased out by the glowlight nook simple touch with glowlight e inkedit main article nook simple touch on april   a nook simple touch reader with builtin led lighting called